,{},[44,153,154],{},"Linux Support",": Specifically designed for Linux environments.",[25,157,63],{"id":62},[38,159,160,166,172],{},[41,161,162,165],{},[44,163,164],{},"VS Code Extension",": Built as an extension for Visual Studio Code.",[41,167,168,171],{},[44,169,170],{},"NASM",": The Netwide Assembler for x86 architecture.",[41,173,174,177],{},[44,175,176],{},"Assembly",": Low-level assembly language programming.",{"title":97,"searchDepth":98,"depth":98,"links":179},[180,181,182],{"id":27,"depth":98,"text":28},{"id":35,"depth":98,"text":36},{"id":62,"depth":98,"text":63},"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/1Q0T-o9AQEvUnEgg5-1Vj_0Qm1ltGwhZI","Vs Code Extension that automates the compilation and execution of assembly codes written in NASM.","https://github.com/Kratosgado/nasm-compiler-linux",[187,183],"https://image2url.com/r2/default/images/1772468211054-abb465e3-17e6-4220-b412-63a35671e73b.png","https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=KratosGado.nasm-compiler-linux",{},{"icon":116},"/projects/nasm-compiler-for-linux",{"title":126,"description":184},"nasm-compiler-for-linux",[164,170,176],"projects/nasm-compiler-for-linux","okvhZFVqpK0Wp4Km0pKNMtTZFCu1rzFOQP16pOCJrwA",{"id":198,"title":199,"body":200,"coverImage":244,"description":245,"extension":105,"github":246,"images":247,"liveUrl":97,"meta":248,"navigation":249,"path":250,"rank":98,"seo":251,"slug":252,"stack":253,"stem":254,"__hash__":255},"projects/projects/pseudo-code-interpreter.md","Pseudo Code Interpreter",{"type":22,"value":201,"toc":239},[202,204,207,209,229,231],[25,203,28],{"id":27},[30,205,206],{},"Pseudo Code Interpreter is a Rust-based tool that interprets and executes pseudo code files passed as command-line arguments. It allows developers to test their algorithms written in pseudo code.",[25,208,36],{"id":35},[38,210,211,217,223],{},[41,212,213,216],{},[44,214,215],{},"Command-Line Interface",": Run pseudo code files from the terminal.",[41,218,219,222],{},[44,220,221],{},"Interpretation",": Executes pseudo code syntax.",[41,224,225,228],{},[44,226,227],{},"Error Handling",": Provides feedback on invalid syntax.",[25,230,63],{"id":62},[38,232,233],{},[41,234,235,238],{},[44,236,237],{},"Rust",": A systems programming language that runs blazingly fast, prevents segfaults, and guarantees thread safety.",{"title":97,"searchDepth":98,"depth":98,"links":240},[241,242,243],{"id":27,"depth":98,"text":28},{"id":35,"depth":98,"text":36},{"id":62,"depth":98,"text":63},"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/16349CIC6DYXDHTwt75gVh1bworLk95VZ","A pseudo code interpreter written in rust that interprets pseudocode file passed to it as cli argument.","https://github.com/Kratosgado/pseudo_interpreter",[],{},{"icon":116},"/projects/pseudo-code-interpreter",{"title":199,"description":245},"pseudo-code-interpreter",[237],"projects/pseudo-code-interpreter","3OvJwE5V_aJ7DZ0Jdn5-jqt5hYmsae-y8gKG1vLvUPw",{"id":257,"title":258,"body":259,"coverImage":244,"description":338,"extension":105,"github":339,"images":340,"liveUrl":342,"meta":343,"navigation":344,"path":345,"rank":98,"seo":346,"slug":347,"stack":348,"stem":349,"__hash__":350},"projects/projects/pseudo-runner.md","Pseudo Runner",{"type":22,"value":260,"toc":332},[261,263,266,268,294,298,306,310],[25,262,28],{"id":27},[30,264,265],{},"Pseudo Runner is a VS Code extension that allows you to write and execute pseudo code directly within the editor. It provides syntax highlighting, code execution, and output display all in one place.",[25,267,36],{"id":35},[38,269,270,276,282,288],{},[41,271,272,275],{},[44,273,274],{},"Syntax Highlighting",": Full pseudo code syntax support",[41,277,278,281],{},[44,279,280],{},"In-Editor Execution",": Run your pseudo code without leaving VS Code",[41,283,284,287],{},[44,285,286],{},"Output Panel",": See execution results in a dedicated output panel",[41,289,290,293],{},[44,291,292],{},"Error Reporting",": Clear error messages with line numbers",[25,295,297],{"id":296},"how-it-works","How It Works",[30,299,300,301,305],{},"The extension registers a custom language mode for ",[302,303,304],"code",{},".pseudo"," files and provides a built-in interpreter that parses and executes the code. Results are displayed in the VS Code output panel.",[25,307,309],{"id":308},"getting-started","Getting Started",[311,312,313,316,322,325],"ol",{},[41,314,315],{},"Install the extension from the VS Code Marketplace",[41,317,318,319,321],{},"Create a new file with the ",[302,320,304],{}," extension",[41,323,324],{},"Write your pseudo code",[41,326,327,328,331],{},"Press ",[302,329,330],{},"Ctrl+Shift+P"," and run \"Pseudo Runner: Execute\"",{"title":97,"searchDepth":98,"depth":98,"links":333},[334,335,336,337],{"id":27,"depth":98,"text":28},{"id":35,"depth":98,"text":36},{"id":296,"depth":98,"text":297},{"id":308,"depth":98,"text":309},"A VS Code extension that runs pseudo code files directly in the editor.","https://github.com/Kratosgado/pseudo-runner",[244,341],"https://image2url.com/r2/default/images/1772468076141-94683d8e-029b-4887-843f-99970e779057.png","https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=KratosGado.pseudo-runner",{},{"icon":116},"/projects/pseudo-runner",{"title":258,"description":338},"pseudo-runner",[82,164],"projects/pseudo-runner","Fh-iPPldsu_FdUn3j8NnzCDw8lzGHbaDVtC-fUZE6rk",{"id":352,"title":353,"body":354,"coverImage":404,"description":405,"extension":105,"github":406,"images":407,"liveUrl":410,"meta":411,"navigation":412,"path":413,"rank":414,"seo":415,"slug":416,"stack":417,"stem":418,"__hash__":419},"projects/projects/bible-studies-wing.md","Bible Studies Wing",{"type":22,"value":355,"toc":399},[356,358,361,363,389,391],[25,357,28],{"id":27},[30,359,360],{},"Bible Studies Wing is a mobile application designed for bible study groups. It allows users to create accounts, read and share bible verses, and connect with other users.",[25,362,36],{"id":35},[38,364,365,371,377,383],{},[41,366,367,370],{},[44,368,369],{},"User Accounts",": C